metadata.name: Princess Tuvstarr
metadata.description: "The fairytale of moose Hop and little princess Tuvstarr" by Helge Kjellin. In the fairytale Tuvstarr goes out to experience the world and she gets help from the moose Hop. He tries to warn her of all the dangers in the forest, but in spite of that, the elves take Tuvstarr's crown and the wood-fairy takes her dress. Finally, she loses her heart of gold in the woodland lake. Tuvstarr sits there by the water forever.
